<section sectnbr = "4E">
<servcat sctnbr = "04" scnbr = "05">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "4">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B4504005" svcinfotypenbr = "06" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
DTC Check
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Confirm that ignition is “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect SUZUKI scan tool to DLC (1).
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L4E001">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "NNNNN-00024">
SUZUKI scan tool (SUZUKI-SDT)
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A460010.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "67.502mm" ver = "01" gw = "159" gh = "175"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Read DTC according to instructions displayed on SUZUKI scan tool and print it or write it down. Refer to SUZUKI scan tool operator’s manual for further details. If communication between scan tool and ABS control module is not possible, check power supply and ground circuits of ABS control module. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4504022"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
 If check result is OK, go to 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70BA804004">Troubleshooting for Communication Bus Off</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Confirm that ignition is “OFF” and disconnect SUZUKI scan tool from DLC after completing check.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
